OL,3,CMan tried but failed to set fire to
OL,4,Cwheelie bin before pushing it at police
OL,6,FThe 22-year-old electrician, of
OL,7,FSalisbury Avenue, Hindley, Wigan, was
OL,8,Fseen on video footage picking up a
OL,9,Fmissile and throwing it at police in
OL,10,Friot gear on the night of 31 July
OL,11,Fafter a protest turned violent.
OL,13,FWhen he was arrested 11 days later,
OL,14,Fsitting in a BMW, he was found to be
OL,15,Fin possession of a small amount of
OL,16,Fcocaine, the court heard.
OL,18,FRachel Masters, prosecuting, said
OL,19,FDixon was working on Teesside at the
OL,20,Ftime and he told police he was present
OL,21,Fthat night "out of curiosity".
